President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey to discuss the situation in Syria and other regional issues. Both leaders expressed their concern about the Syrian government's use of violence against civilians and emphasized the importance of meeting the Syrian people's legitimate demands for a transition to democracy. They also called for an immediate halt to the bloodshed and violence in Syria. The two leaders agreed to closely monitor the actions of the Syrian government and to consult with each other in the future. Additionally, they pledged to coordinate their efforts in responding to the famine in the horn of Africa and to increase assistance to save lives.